# Git & Workflow

## Commit Style
- Conventional commits: `feat:`, `fix:`, `chore:`, `docs:`, `refactor:`
- Scope with package name: `feat(centerdevice):`, `fix(core):`, `chore(bidrento):`
- Short imperative subject (max 72 chars)
- Body explains WHY, not WHAT
- One logical change per commit

## Branch Strategy
- `main` is production — always deployable
- Feature branches: `feat/short-description`
- Fix branches: `fix/short-description`
- No long-lived branches — merge fast, deploy fast

## Pre-commit Checklist
1. `npm run build` passes (all workspaces)
2. `npm test` passes (47+ tests)
3. No `console.log` left — use core logger
4. `.env` / secrets not staged
5. TypeScript strict mode clean

## Repo Hygiene
- `docs/ARCHITECTURE.md` is the source of truth — update when adding services/tools
- `.env.example` per service package
- Keep `package-lock.json` committed
